c=\"/writing/assets/static/leavesgif.bd6740a.195189c5eb8a924335e9f359dbe0ae0d.gif\" width=\"600\" alt=\"leavesgif\"></noscript></p>\n<p>The best part about them is how they separate my website from so many other portfolio sites. I don't think my website design is all that great, but these leaves bring a wow factor. As I built and designed websites for friends and tas.health's Shopify store, that wow factor was centered in my mind.</p>\n<p>For the web, a simple library will be able to bring animations, and with Shopify, an app. So it became a mission, starting with my already made leavesüçÉ.</p>\n<h2 id=\"javascript\"><a href=\"#javascript\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"icon icon-link\"></span></a>JavaScript</h2>\n<h5 id=\"vanilla\"><a href=\"#vanilla\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"icon icon-link\"></span></a>Vanilla</h5>\n<p>The leaves animation on my website is built using jQuery. For the library I remade it using vanilla Javascript, this is because I want the library to be as light-weight as possible. With vanilla Javascript, the libraries only dependency is GSAP. <a href=\"https://github.com/arjunkalburgi/arjunanimation_leaves/commit/5a7dfb9ca15a59d60ead48646bc3387329782930\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">Peep the commit.</a></p>\n<h5 id=\"style\"><a href=\"#style\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"icon icon-link\"></span></a>Style</h5>\n<p>For the library to be even easier to use, I moved all the CSS into the JS of the library using <code class=\"language-text\">document.createElement(&#39;style&#39;);</code> and appending it to the <code class=\"language-text\">head</code> tag. <a href=\"https://github.com/arjunkalburgi/arjunanimation_leaves/commit/6526aad1e08eaf757cf30c4f6ae1222109068728\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">Peep the commit.</a></p>\n<h5 id=\"umd\"><a href=\"#umd\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"icon icon-link\"></span></a>UMD</h5>\n<p>I had to learn what a Universal Module Definition is, but the concept is pretty easy. It's a wrapper for your library such that it's good to go in a variety of other's' code environments. There's a line for module system's such as <code class=\"language-text\">npm</code>, something for <code class=\"language-text\">require</code>, and the default for <code class=\"language-text\">static</code>. <a href=\"https://github.com/arjunkalburgi/arjunanimation_leaves/commit/ce9f6d32521e1a880de94d0114bb26a582d6fd77\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">Peep the commit.</a></p>\n<h5 id=\"customization\"><a href=\"#customization\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"icon icon-link\"></span></a>Customization</h5>\n<p>The package needs some flexibility so users can have some customization. I modified the animation function to accept a custom <code class=\"language-text\">className</code> for the animation to work on, a custom number of leaves that are created and custom sprites that the animation will animate. </p>\n<div class=\"gridsome-highlight\" data-language=\"javascript\"><pre class=\"language-javascript\"><code class=\"language-javascript\">arjunanimation_leaves<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">animate</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n    <span class=\"token comment\">// identify the class name of the element you want the animaiton to appear within</span>\n    <span class=\"token comment\">//      the leaves will not show outside this container</span>\n    className<span class=\"token operator\">:</span> <span class=\"token string\">'arjunanimation_leaves'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> \n\n    <span class=\"token comment\">// identify the number of sprites you would like to appear within the container</span>\n    numOfSprites<span class=\"token operator\">:</span> <span class=\"token number\">30</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n\n    <span class=\"token comment\">// define the sprites using an array of paths</span>\n    pathsOfSprites<span class=\"token operator\">:</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">[</span>\n        <span class=\"token string\">'./element01.svg'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n        <span class=\"token string\">'./element02.svg'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n        <span class=\"token string\">'./element03.svg'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n        <span class=\"token string\">'./element04.svg'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n        <span class=\"token string\">'./element05.svg'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n        <span class=\"token string\">'./element06.svg'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n        <span class=\"token string\">'./element07.svg'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n        <span class=\"token string\">'./element08.svg'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n    <span class=\"token punctuation\">]</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span></code></pre></div>\n<h2 id=\"npm\"><a href=\"#npm\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"icon icon-link\"></span></a>NPM</h2>\n<p>After I added a static and VueJS example and some documentation, I got to working on publishing the library to NPMjs.com. </p>\n<h5 id=\"npmignore\"><a href=\"#npmignore\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"icon icon-link\"></span></a>.npmignore</h5>\n<p>I added an <code class=\"language-text\">.npmignore</code> file to my package to remove the examples folder from the package. Since the examples folder has a VueJS app in it, it takes up lots of space relative to how small the package itself is.</p>\n<h5 id=\"scoped-org\"><a href=\"#scoped-org\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"icon icon-link\"></span></a>Scoped Org</h5>\n<p>After publishing initially, I ended up republishing using a scoped organization. Scopes allow you to create a package with the same name as a package created by another user or Org without conflict. This way I don't have to have a long library name (it was <code class=\"language-text\">arjunanimation_leaves</code>). </p>\n<p>I made my organization name <code class=\"language-text\">@arjunanimations</code> and my package name <code class=\"language-text\">leaves</code>, for the full effect of <code class=\"language-text\">@arjunanimations/leaves</code>.</p>\n<h5 id=\"it-works\"><a href=\"#it-works\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"icon icon-link\"></span></a>It works!</h5>\n<p>Now you can <code class=\"language-text\">npm i @arjunanimations/leaves</code> to add it to your project :D </p>\n<h2 id=\"whats-next\"><a href=\"#whats-next\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"icon icon-link\"></span></a>What's Next?</h2>\n<p>I need to make the Shopify app so that businesses can add leaves to their site! I also want to add examples for React and Angular to the documentation. </p>\n<p>If you know how to make Shopify apps, help me out! Finding it confusing so far üòÖ</p>\n<p><img class=\"g-image g-image--lazy g-image--loading\" src=\"data:image/svg+xml,%3csvg fill='none' viewBox='0 0 600 300' xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg' xmlns:xlink='http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink'%3e%3cdefs%3e%3cfilter id='__svg-blur-4efeb9242917007a3a8e103369924e0c'%3e%3cfeGaussianBlur in='SourceGraphic' stdDeviation='40'/%3e%3c/filter%3e%3c/defs%3e%3cimage x='0' y='0' filter='url(%23__svg-blur-4efeb9242917007a3a8e103369924e0c)' width='600' height='300' xlink:href='data:image/gif%3bbase64%2ciVBORw0KGgoAAAANSUhEUgAAAEAAAAAgCAYAAACinX6EAAAACXBIWXMAAAPoAAAD6AG1e1JrAAAGK0lEQVRo3rVZaZObRhDl//%2bffElVUqlKKvmQy157vfLeWmm1ugUCAdIA7X4NAwNCAknI5SlxzDQzfbx%2b3WslUUJdD%2bKhooi2SlEUxXJ/qoyY111jb6nsQr7VreBUKA4/CW2633zQbOvIfd2hcK9HVQZFdBUlxGIQygYrIFa8gQ4HhAZqR8NgQQ%2bsgCkrIFBbeW7O054i3qESYz2Rv9vSInRTJXS%2bP6Ll1pX97dhDreu4WMyWX9OrP%2bWPeeJyhdZJ5iA0QlbULFzzRqLc4lDImL3naTOR9%2bnzDvcXJ/T3%